spin:MagicProperty.rdfs:comment:
Takes an instance (?arg1) and a class definition (?arg2) and returns all constraint violations for that instance as triples. This magic property basically runs its own constraint checker for defining meta-constraints, and can also be used to classify instances.

Example:

    CONSTRUCT {
        ?s ?p ?o .
    }
    WHERE {
        (my:Person my:OldPerson) spin:constructViolations (?s ?p ?o) .
    }
